y unique , and the lack of information available about the distribution of speech features in the population as a whole . ^ detailed research into aspects of speech that might be used to differentiate individuals is greatly needed . ^ some examples of features of speech which have been shown to exhibit speaker-specific behaviour include fundamental frequencies , formant frequencies , aspects of coarticulation , degree of nasality , voice quality and phonation types , intonation , rate of speech , pauses and hesitation marks . ^ this talk will include a brief outline of research into the speaker-characterising properties of formant dynamics , and how this further work in this area should contribute to the knowledge base from which forensic phonetic evidence can be drawn . ^ * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *  ame east research  ame for english and  ame  ame university of  ame </text_normal></part></message_body></message>